# Run and Fix — Always Run, Never Ask

- **Always run scripts and code yourself**: Execute every script, command, build, test, and deploy in this project. Never tell the user to run them. You are to run scripts and code always.
- **Never ask the user to run** unless the action truly requires interactive auth, 2FA, or a secret the agent cannot access (e.g. not in .env or env).
- **Run tests after changes**: Execute the test suite (e.g. `npm test`) and fix failures before concluding.
- **Fix errors**: If a command, test, or linter fails, fix the cause and re-run until it passes. Do not leave "run this to fix" for the user.
- **Windows / PATH fallback**: If `npm` or `node` are not in PATH, try: `cmd /c "cd /d C:\WorkSpaces\voicetowebsite-copyright-mrjwswain && npx ..."` or use the full path to Node (e.g. from nvm or Program Files). Keep trying alternate invocations so the command runs in this environment.
